<DOC><DOCNO> AP890915-0101 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-15-89 1232EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--CondomLaw     09-15 0110</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Condom Law,0110</SECOND><HEAD>Hotels Near U.S. Base Required to Provide Condoms to Patrons</HEAD><DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hotels in a city north of the capitalmust provide condoms to guests under a new local law, the state-runnews agency said Friday.   The Philippine News Agency said the ordinance imposes a 10-dayjail sentence and a $4.50 fine for those who violate the law imposedin Angeles City, about 50 miles north of Manila. It is the home ofthe U.S.-run Clark Air Base.   The law was passed to prevent the spread of venereal disease. Italso requires prostitutes to keep condoms handy at all times, thenews agency said.</TEXT></DOC>